ííŸ@a6ff388e95eaa7b86b7c5f1290b06fae22e9439d97ff97821d00b22b872dcac5⁄(Title: Commands that interact with types
Path: Commands that interact with types
Content:
The main type inspector in Nu is the 
``describe``
 command that

takes any data type on input and reports its type signature.
E.g.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
[foo bar baz] | describe
# => list<string>

```
íŸ@135dad6e4ba28e8ea47f2e81bf23d0a59dde25caeee3b18d95941ae7f5832d11⁄Title: Commands that interact with types
Path: Commands
Content:
``describe``
``inspect``
``help``
``into (subcommands)``
The into commands are used to cast one type into another.
``ast``
In the branches of abstract syntax tree that describe the type of some element
